1933;;Mama Loves Papa;;American;;Norman Z. McLeod;;Charlie Ruggles, Mary Boland;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mama_Loves_Papa_(1933_film);;While Wilbur Todd (Charlie Ruggles) is content with his middle class life, his wife Jessie (Mary Boland) aspires to a higher social stannding. She insists he wear fine clothes because she believes that clothes make the man. When his strange new clothes bring derision rather than admiration, and tired of his wife's constant nagging, Wilbur goes off on a drunken spree and innocently becomes involved with the village vamp, Mrs. McIntosh (Lilyan Tashman).